SIMPLE: absolutist
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Absolutist
<hw>Ab"so*lu`tist</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who is in favor of an absolute or autocratic
government.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Metaph.)</fld> <def>One who believes that it is
possible to realize a cognition or concept of <xex>the
absolute</xex>.</def> <rj><au>Sir. W. Hamilton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Absolutist</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Absolutist
<hw>Ab"so*lu`tist</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
absolutism; arbitrary; despotic; <as>as, <ex>absolutist</ex>
principles</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Absolutistic</ent>⟦br⟧
